	   <tr><td colspan=2>The crystallized shadow armor is mostly crap. The weight is a bit too high. The legs here are the only really good bit. The best a Monk can really expect to get at this level range without having a lot of higher level friends help him is the Gatorscale Leggings. If you are a Monk, to put it mildy, the GS legs get very old after you've worn them for 15 levels. These offer a very nice new look, one more point of AC, and some small bonuses for combat stats that are better than the bonuses on the Gatorscale Leggings. They also weigh a hell of a lot more, but once a Monk gets a set of Tink bags (which they can easily do in a week at level 45) the extra weight isn't so bad. I'd wear a pair of these. They're the best drop armor that you can get except for the hard to find oiled greaves and the velious quest armors.<br><br>I'd say it s a question of fashion if you really want to wear these. Same goes for the tunic which is the only other decent Monk piece, but the tunic weighs 5.0 and not many Monks will go for that.<br><br>Raviel Darkfyre<br>51 Disciple, Luclin<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
